<div id="review_2719099728" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2719099728" />
    <a title="Bonnie Gutzman" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/24133283-bonnie-gutzman"><img alt="Bonnie Gutzman" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1560998666p2/24133283.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2719099728?book_show_action=true">Feb 17, 2019</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Bonnie Gutzman" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Bonnie Gutzman" href="/user/show/24133283-bonnie-gutzman">Bonnie Gutzman</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2719099728" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer5157311837216287703">I like the story but it seems like I am just reading the same things over and over. The book rotates between several characters and each time it comes back around to a character the story seems to be the same as the last time around with that character. It’s probably how it was in the war - the same awful, difficult things being experienced over and over for days and weeks and years.</span>

          </span>
        </div>


